Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine orange-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 124 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name Teisamenos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0528. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1148)
